identification.name: identification
identification.description: The identification package describes a model of references and identifiers for information entities.

ARCHETYPE_ID.name: ARCHETYPE_ID
ARCHETYPE_ID.description:
Identifier for archetypes. Ideally these would identify globally unique archetypes.
Lexical form: `rm_originator  '-' rm_name  '-' rm_entity  '.' concept_name {  '-' specialisation }*  '.v' number`.

qualified_rm_entity.name: qualified_rm_entity
qualified_rm_entity.description: Globally qualified reference model entity, e.g.  `openehr-EHR-OBSERVATION`.

domain_concept.name: domain_concept
domain_concept.description: Name of the concept represented by this archetype, including specialisation, e.g. `Biochemistry_result-cholesterol`.

rm_originator.name: rm_originator
rm_originator.description: Organisation originating the reference model on which this archetype is based, e.g. openehr,  cen,  hl7 .

rm_name.name: rm_name
rm_name.description: Name of the reference model, e.g. rim,  ehr_rm,  en13606 .

rm_entity.name: rm_entity
rm_entity.description: Name of the ontological level within the reference model to which this archetype is targeted, e.g. for openEHR,  folder ,  composition ,  section ,  entry .

specialisation.name: specialisation
specialisation.description: Name of specialisation of concept, if this archetype is a specialisation of another archetype, e.g.  cholesterol .

GENERIC_ID.name: GENERIC_ID
GENERIC_ID.description: Generic identifier type for identifiers whose format is otherwise unknown to openEHR. Includes an attribute for naming the identification scheme (which may well be local).

scheme.name: scheme
scheme.description: Name of the scheme to which this identifier conforms. Ideally this name will be recognisable globally but realistically it may be a local ad hoc scheme whose name is not controlled or standardised in any way.

HIER_OBJECT_ID.name: HIER_OBJECT_ID
HIER_OBJECT_ID.description: Concrete type corresponding to hierarchical identifiers of the form defined by UID_BASED_ID.

LOCATABLE_REF.name: LOCATABLE_REF
LOCATABLE_REF.description: Purpose Reference to a `LOCATABLE` instance inside the top-level content structure inside a `VERSION<T>`; the path attribute is applied to the object that `VERSION._data_` points to.

path.name: path
path.description: The path to an instance in question, as an absolute path with respect to the object found at `VERSION._data_`. An empty path means that the object referred to by id being specified.

id.name: id
id.description: Globally unique id of an object, regardless of where it is stored.

as_uri.name: as_uri
as_uri.description:
A URI form of the reference, created by concatenating the following: 

* scheme, e.g. `ehr:`, derived from `_namespace_`
* `_id.value_`
* `/` + `_path_`, where `_path_` is non-empty

OBJECT_ID.name: OBJECT_ID
OBJECT_ID.description:
Ancestor class of identifiers of informational objects. Ids may be completely meaningless, in which case their only job is to refer to something, or may carry some information to do with the identified object. 

Object ids are used inside an object to identify that object. To identify another object in another service, use an `OBJECT_REF`, or else use a UID for local objects identified by UID. If none of the subtypes is suitable, direct instances of this class may be used.

value.name: value
value.description: The value of the id in the form defined below.

OBJECT_REF.name: OBJECT_REF
OBJECT_REF.description: Class describing a reference to another object, which may exist locally or be maintained outside the current namespace, e.g. in another service. Services are usually external, e.g. available in a LAN (including on the same host) or the internet via Corba, SOAP, or some other distributed protocol. However, in small systems they may be part of the same executable as the data containing the Id.

namespace.name: namespace
namespace.description:
Namespace to which this identifier belongs in the local system context (and possibly in any other openEHR compliant environment) e.g.  terminology ,  demographic . These names are not yet standardised. Legal values for `_namespace_` are:

* `"local"`
* `"unknown"`
* a string matching the regex `[a-zA-Z][a-zA-Z0-9_-:/&+?]*`

type.name: type
type.description: Name of the  class (concrete or abstract) of object to which this identifier type refers, e.g. `PARTY`, `PERSON`,  `GUIDELINE`  etc. These class names are from the relevant reference model. The type name `ANY` can be used to indicate that any type is accepted (e.g. if the type is unknown).

id.name: id
id.description: Globally unique id of an object, regardless of where it is stored.

OBJECT_VERSION_ID.name: OBJECT_VERSION_ID
OBJECT_VERSION_ID.description: Globally unique identifier for one version of a versioned object; lexical form: `object_id  '::' creating_system_id  '::' version_tree_id`.

object_id.name: object_id
object_id.description: Unique identifier for logical object of which this identifier identifies one version; normally the `_object_id_` will be the unique identifier of the version container containing the version referred to by this `OBJECT_VERSION_ID` instance.

version_tree_id.name: version_tree_id
version_tree_id.description: Tree identifier of this version with respect to other versions in the same version tree, as either 1 or 3 part dot-separated numbers, e.g.  1 ,  2.1.4 .

creating_system_id.name: creating_system_id
creating_system_id.description: Identifier of the system that created the Version corresponding to this Object version id.

is_branch.name: is_branch
is_branch.description: True if this version identifier represents a branch.

PARTY_REF.name: PARTY_REF
PARTY_REF.description: Identifier for parties in a demographic or identity service. There are typically a number of subtypes of the `PARTY` class, including `PERSON`, `ORGANISATION`, etc. Abstract supertypes are allowed if the referenced object is of a type not known by the current implementation of this class (in other words, if the demographic model is changed by the addition of a new `PARTY` or `ACTOR` subtypes, valid `PARTY_REFs` can still be constructed to them).

Type_validity.name: Type_validity
Type_validity.rule: type.is_equal(“PERSON”) or type.is_equal(“ORGANISATION”) or type.is_equal(“GROUP”) or type.is_equal(“AGENT”)or type.is_equal(“ROLE”) or type.is_equal(“PARTY”) or type.is_equal(“ACTOR”)

TERMINOLOGY_ID.name: TERMINOLOGY_ID
TERMINOLOGY_ID.description:
Identifier for terminologies such as accessed via a terminology query service. In this class, the value attribute identifies the Terminology in the terminology service, e.g.  SNOMED-CT . A terminology is assumed to be in a particular language, which must be explicitly specified.

The value if the id attribute is the precise terminology id identifier, including actual release (i.e. actual  version), local modifications etc; e.g. ICPC2.

Lexical form: `name [  '(' version  ')' ]`.

name.name: name
name.description: Return the terminology id (which includes the  version  in some cases). Distinct names correspond to distinct (i.e. non-compatible) terminologies. Thus the names  ICD10AM  and  ICD10  refer to distinct terminologies.

version_id.name: version_id
version_id.description: Version of this terminology, if versioning supported, else the empty string.

VERSION_TREE_ID.name: VERSION_TREE_ID
VERSION_TREE_ID.description:
Version tree identifier for one version. Lexical form: 

`trunk_version [  '.' branch_number  '.' branch_version ]`

trunk_version.name: trunk_version
trunk_version.description: Trunk version number; numbering starts at 1.

is_branch.name: is_branch
is_branch.description: True if this version identifier represents a branch, i.e. has branch_number and branch_version parts.

branch_number.name: branch_number
branch_number.description: Number of branch from the trunk point; numbering starts at 1.

branch_version.name: branch_version
branch_version.description: Version of the branch; numbering starts at 1.

Trunk_version_valid.name: Trunk_version_valid
Trunk_version_valid.rule: trunk_version /= Void and then trunk_version.is_integer and then trunk_version.as_integer >= 1

Branch_number_valid.name: Branch_number_valid
Branch_number_valid.rule: branch_number /= Void implies branch_number.is_integer and then branch_number.as_integer >= 1

Branch_version_valid.name: Branch_version_valid
Branch_version_valid.rule: branch_version /= Void implies branch_version.is_integer and then branch_version.as_integer >= 1

Branch_validity.name: Branch_validity
Branch_validity.rule: (branch_number = Void and branch_version = Void ) xor (branch_number /= Void and branch_version /= Void )

UID_BASED_ID.name: UID_BASED_ID
UID_BASED_ID.description:
Abstract model of UID-based identifiers consisting of a root part and an optional extension;

lexical form: `root '::' extension`.

root.name: root
root.description: The identifier of the conceptual namespace in which the object exists, within the identification scheme. Returns the part to the left of the first '::' separator, if any, or else the whole string.

extension.name: extension
extension.description: Optional local identifier of the object within the context of the root identifier. Returns the part to the right of the first '::' separator if any, or else any empty String.

UUID.name: UUID
UUID.description: Model of the DCE Universal Unique Identifier or UUID which takes the form of hexadecimal integers separated by hyphens, following the pattern 8-4-4-4-12 as defined by the Open Group, CDE 1.1 Remote Procedure Call specification, Appendix A. Also known as a GUID.

INTERNET_ID.name: INTERNET_ID
INTERNET_ID.description: Model of a reverse internet domain, as used to uniquely identify an internet domain. In the form of a dot-separated string in the reverse order of a domain name, specified by http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc1034.txt[IETF RFC 1034^].

UID.name: UID
UID.description: Abstract parent of classes representing unique identifiers which identify information entities in a durable way. UIDs only ever identify one IE in time or space and are never re-used.

ISO_OID.name: ISO_OID
ISO_OID.description: Model of ISO's Object Identifier (oid) as defined by the standard ISO/IEC 8824. Oids are formed from integers separated by dots. Each non-leaf node in an Oid starting from the left corresponds to an assigning authority, and identifies that authority's namespace, inside which the remaining part of the identifier is locally unique.

TEMPLATE_ID.name: TEMPLATE_ID
TEMPLATE_ID.description: Identifier for templates. Lexical form to be determined.

ACCESS_GROUP_REF.name: ACCESS_GROUP_REF
ACCESS_GROUP_REF.description: Reference to access group in an access control service.

definitions.name: definitions
definitions.description: The rm.support.definition package defines symbolic definitions used by the openEHR models. Only a small number are currently defined.

OPENEHR_DEFINITIONS.name: OPENEHR_DEFINITIONS
OPENEHR_DEFINITIONS.description: Inheritance class to provide access to constants defined in other packages.

Local_terminology_id.name: Local_terminology_id
Local_terminology_id.description: Predefined terminology identifier to indicate it is local to the knowledge resource in which it occurs, e.g. an archetype

VALIDITY_KIND.name: VALIDITY_KIND
VALIDITY_KIND.description:
An enumeration of three values that may commonly occur in constraint models.

Use as the type of any attribute within this model, which expresses constraint on some attribute in a class in a reference model. For example to indicate validity
of Date/Time fields.

VERSION_STATUS.name: VERSION_STATUS
VERSION_STATUS.description: Status of a versioned artefact, as one of a number of possible values: uncontrolled, prerelease, release, build.

Hash.name: Hash
Hash.description: Type representing a keyed table of values. V is the value type, and K the type of the keys.

has_key.name: has_key
has_key.description: Test for membership of a key.

Hash<String, Hash<String, String>>.name: Hash<String, Hash<String, String>>
Hash<String, Hash<String, String>>.description: Two-level hash map structure, typically used for two levels of keyed tables, e.g. with outer keys = language ("en", "zh" etc) and inner keys = some tag or id or path.

Container.name: Container
Container.description: Abstract ancestor of container types whose items are addressable in some way.

has.name: has
has.description: Test for membership of a value.

List.name: List
List.description: Ordered container that may contain duplicates.

Set.name: Set
Set.description: Unordered container that may not contain duplicates.

Array.name: Array
Array.description: Container whose storage is assumed to be contiguous.

primitive_types.name: primitive_types
primitive_types.description: Some primitive/built-in types for the openEHR Reference Model.

Ordered_Numeric.name: Ordered_Numeric
Ordered_Numeric.description: Abstract notional parent class of ordered, numeric types, which are types with ‘<‘ and arithmetic operators defined.

Integer.name: Integer
Integer.description: Class representing minimal interface of standard Integer type.

Numeric.name: Numeric
Numeric.description: Abstract notional parent class of numeric types, which are types which have various arithmetic and comparison operators defined.

infix *.name: infix *
infix *.description: Product by `other'. Actual type of result depends on arithmetic balancing rules.

infix +.name: infix +
infix +.description: Sum with `other' (commutative). Actual type of result depends on arithmetic balancing rules.

infix -.name: infix -
infix -.description: Result of subtracting `other'. Actual type of result depends on arithmetic balancing rules.

Boolean.name: Boolean
Boolean.description: Class representing minimal interface of standard Boolean type.

Post_de_Morgan.name: Post_de_Morgan
Post_de_Morgan.rule: Result = not (not self or not other)

Post_de_Morgan.name: Post_de_Morgan
Post_de_Morgan.rule: Result = not (not self or else not other)

Post_de_Morgan.name: Post_de_Morgan
Post_de_Morgan.rule: Result = not (not self and not other)

Post_de_Morgan.name: Post_de_Morgan
Post_de_Morgan.rule: Result = not (not self and then not other)

Post_definition.name: Post_definition
Post_definition.rule: Result = ((self or other) and not (self and other))

String.name: String
String.description: Strings of characters, as used to represent textual data in any natural or formal language.

infix +.name: infix +
infix +.description: Concatenation operator - causes ‘other’ to be appended to this string.

is_empty.name: is_empty
is_empty.description: True if string is empty, i.e. equal to "".

is_integer.name: is_integer
is_integer.description: True if string can be parsed as an integer.

as_integer.name: as_integer
as_integer.description: Return the integer corresponding to the integer value represented in this string.

Real.name: Real
Real.description: Type used to represent decimal numbers. Corresponds to a single-precision floating point value in most languages.

floor.name: floor
floor.description: Return the greatest integer no greater than the value of this object.

Integer64.name: Integer64
Integer64.description: Class representing minimal interface of standard Integer64 type.

Ordered.name: Ordered
Ordered.description: Abstract notional parent class of ordered, types i.e. types on which the ‘<‘ operator is defined.

infix <.name: infix <
infix <.description: Arithmetic comparison. In conjunction with ‘=’, enables the definition of the operators ‘>’, ‘>=’, ‘<=’, ‘<>’. In real type systems, this operator might be defined on another class for comparability.

TUPLE.name: TUPLE
TUPLE.description: Parent type of all TUPLE types.

FUNCTION.name: FUNCTION
FUNCTION.description: Type representing a function with a return type and 0 or more arguments represented as a TUPLE.

TUPLE1.name: TUPLE1
TUPLE1.description: A Tuple type used, among other things, for representing a single typed argument within a Routine signature.

TUPLE2.name: TUPLE2
TUPLE2.description: A Tuple type used, among other things, for representing two typed arguments within a Routine signature.

ROUTINE.name: ROUTINE
ROUTINE.description: Type representing a function with a return type and 0 or more arguments represented as a TUPLE.

PROCEDURE.name: PROCEDURE
PROCEDURE.description: Type representing a procedure with 0 or more arguments represented as a TUPLE.

Iso8601_date_time.name: Iso8601_date_time
Iso8601_date_time.description:
Represents an ISO 8601 date/time, including partial and extended forms. Value may be:

* `YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[,sss][Z | ±hh[mm]]` (extended, preferred) or
* `YYYYMMDDThhmmss[,sss][Z | ±hh[mm]]` (compact)
* or a partial variant.

See `_valid_iso8601_date_time()_` for validity.

Note that this class includes 2 deviations from ISO 8601:2004:

* for partial date/times, any part of the date/time up to the month may be missing, not just seconds and minutes as in the standard;
* the time `24:00:00` is not allowed, since it would mean the date was really on the next day.

month_unknown.name: month_unknown
month_unknown.description: Indicates whether month in year is unknown.

day_unknown.name: day_unknown
day_unknown.description: Indicates whether day in month is unknown.

minute_unknown.name: minute_unknown
minute_unknown.description: Indicates whether minute in hour is known.

second_unknown.name: second_unknown
second_unknown.description: Indicates whether minute in hour is known.

is_decimal_sign_comma.name: is_decimal_sign_comma
is_decimal_sign_comma.description: True if this time has a decimal part indicated by ‘,’ (comma) rather than ‘.’ (period).

is_partial.name: is_partial
is_partial.description: True if this date time is partial, i.e. if seconds or more is missing.

is_extended.name: is_extended
is_extended.description: True if this date/time uses ‘-’, ‘:’ separators.

has_fractional_second.name: has_fractional_second
has_fractional_second.description: True if the fractional_second part is signficant (i.e. even if = 0.0).

as_string.name: as_string
as_string.description: Return the string value in extended format.

Iso8601_duration.name: Iso8601_duration
Iso8601_duration.description:
Represents an ISO 8601 duration, which may have multiple parts from years down to seconds. Value is in format:

* `P[nnY][nnM][nnW][nnD][T[nnH][nnM][nnS]]`

is_decimal_sign_comma.name: is_decimal_sign_comma
is_decimal_sign_comma.description: True if this time has a decimal part indicated by ',' (comma) rather than '.' (period).

years.name: years
years.description: Number of years of nominal 365-day length.

to_seconds.name: to_seconds
to_seconds.description: Total number of seconds equivalent (including fractional) of entire duration.

Iso8601_time.name: Iso8601_time
Iso8601_time.description:
Represents an ISO 8601 time, including partial and extended forms. Value may be:

* `hh:mm:ss[,sss][Z|±hh[mm]]` (extended, preferred) or
* `hhmmss[,sss][Z|±hh[mm]]` (compact)
* or a partial invariant.

See `_valid_iso8601_time()_` for validity.

NOTE: A small deviation to the ISO 8601:2004 standard in this class is that the time `24:00:00` is not allowed, for consistency with `Iso8601_date_time`.

minute_unknown.name: minute_unknown
minute_unknown.description: Indicates whether minute is unknown. If so, the time is of the form “hh”.

second_unknown.name: second_unknown
second_unknown.description: Indicates whether second is unknown. If so and month is known, the time is of the form `"hh:mm"` or `"hhmm"`.

is_decimal_sign_comma.name: is_decimal_sign_comma
is_decimal_sign_comma.description: True if this time has a decimal part indicated by ‘,’ (comma) rather than ‘.’ (period).

is_partial.name: is_partial
is_partial.description: True if this time is partial, i.e. if seconds or more is missing.

is_extended.name: is_extended
is_extended.description: True if this time uses ‘-’, ‘:’ separators.

has_fractional_second.name: has_fractional_second
has_fractional_second.description: True if the fractional_second part is signficant (i.e. even if = 0.0).

as_string.name: as_string
as_string.description: Return string value in extended format.

Iso8601_timezone.name: Iso8601_timezone
Iso8601_timezone.description:
ISO8601 timezone string, in format:

* `Z | ±hh[mm]`

where:

* `hh` is "00" - "23" (0-filled to two digits)
* `mm` is "00" - "59" (0-filled to two digits)
* `Z` is a literal meaning UTC (modern replacement for GMT), i.e. timezone `+0000`

hour.name: hour
hour.description: Hour part of timezone - in the range 00 - 13.

minute.name: minute
minute.description: Minute part of timezone. Generally 00 or 30.

sign.name: sign
sign.description: Direction of timezone expresssed as +1 or -1.

is_partial.name: is_partial
is_partial.description: True if this time zone is partial, i.e. if minutes is missing.

is_extended.name: is_extended
is_extended.description: True if this time-zone uses ‘:’ separators.

is_gmt.name: is_gmt
is_gmt.description: True if timezone is UTC, i.e. +0000.

Min_hour_valid.name: Min_hour_valid
Min_hour_valid.rule: sign = -1 implies hour > 0 and hour <= Min_timezone_hour

Max_hour_valid.name: Max_hour_valid
Max_hour_valid.rule: sign = 1 implies hour > 0 and hour <= Max_timezone_hour

Iso8601_type.name: Iso8601_type
Iso8601_type.description: Abstract ancestor type of ISO 8601 types, defining interface for 'extended' and 'partial' concepts from ISO 8601.

value.name: value
value.description: Representation of all descendants is a single String.

is_partial.name: is_partial
is_partial.description: True if this date time is partial, i.e. if trailing end (right hand) value(s) is/are missing.

is_extended.name: is_extended
is_extended.description: True if this ISO8601 string is in the 'extended' form, i.e. uses ‘-’ and / or ‘:’ separators. This is the preferred format.

Iso8601_date.name: Iso8601_date
Iso8601_date.description:
Represents an ISO 8601 date, including partial and extended forms. Value may be:

* `YYYY-MM-DD` (extended, preferred)
* `YYYYMMDD` (compactd)
* a partial invariant.

See `Time_definitions._valid_iso8601_date()_` for validity.

month_unknown.name: month_unknown
month_unknown.description: Indicates whether month in year is unknown. If so, the date is of the form `"YYYY"`.

day_unknown.name: day_unknown
day_unknown.description: Indicates whether day in month is unknown. If so, and month is known, the date is of the form `"YYYY-MM"` or `"YYYYMM"`.

is_partial.name: is_partial
is_partial.description: True if this date is partial, i.e. if days or more is missing.

is_extended.name: is_extended
is_extended.description: True if this date uses `'-'` separators.

as_string.name: as_string
as_string.description: Return string value in extended format.

Day_valid.name: Day_valid
Day_valid.rule: not day_unknown implies valid_day (year, month, day)

Time_Definitions.name: Time_Definitions
Time_Definitions.description: Definitions for date/time classes. Note that the timezone limits are set by where the international dateline is. Thus, time in New Zealand is quoted using `+12:00`, not `-12:00`.

Nominal_days_in_month.name: Nominal_days_in_month
Nominal_days_in_month.description: Used for conversions of durations containing months to days and / or seconds.

Nominal_days_in_year.name: Nominal_days_in_year
Nominal_days_in_year.description: Used for conversions of durations containing years to days and / or seconds.

Min_timezone_hour.name: Min_timezone_hour
Min_timezone_hour.description: Minimum hour value of a timezone (note that the -ve sign is supplied in the ISO8601_TIMEZONE class).

valid_day.name: valid_day
valid_day.description: True if d >= 1 and d <= days_in_month (m, y)

Post.name: Post
Post.rule: Result = d >= 1 and d <= days_in_month (m, y)

valid_hour.name: valid_hour
valid_hour.description: True if (h >= 0 and h < Hours_in_day) or (h = Hours_in_day and m = 0 and s = 0)

Post.name: Post
Post.rule: Result = (h >= 0 and h < Hours_in_day) or (h = Hours_in_day and m = 0 and s = 0)

valid_minute.name: valid_minute
valid_minute.description: True if m >= 0 and m < Minutes_in_hour.

valid_second.name: valid_second
valid_second.description: True if s >= 0 and s < Seconds_in_minute .

valid_iso8601_date.name: valid_iso8601_date
valid_iso8601_date.description:
String is a valid ISO 8601 date, i.e. takes the complete form:

* `YYYY-MM-DD` (extended, preferred) or one of the partial forms `YYYY-MM` or `YYYY`
* `YYYYMMDD` (compact) or a partial variant `YYYYMM`.

Where:

* `YYYY` is the string form of any positive number in the range `0000` - `9999` (zero-filled to four digits)
* `MM` is `01` - `12` (zero-filled to two digits)
* `DD` is `01` - `31` (zero-filled to two digits)

The combinations of `YYYY`, `MM`, `DD` numbers must be correct with respect to the Gregorian calendar.

valid_iso8601_time.name: valid_iso8601_time
valid_iso8601_time.description:
String is a valid ISO 8601 date, i.e. takes the form:

* `hh:mm:ss[(,|.)s+][Z|±hh[:mm]]` (extended)
* `hhmmss[(,|.)s+][Z|±hh[mm]]` (compact)
* or one of the partial forms:
** `hh:mm` (extended)
** `hhmm` or `hh` (compact)

with an additional optional timezone indicator of:

* `Z` or`±hh[:mm]` (extended)  `±hh[mm]` (compact)

Where:

* `hh` is "00" - "23" (0-filled to two digits)
* `mm` is "00" - "59" (0-filled to two digits)
* `ss` is "00" - "60" (0-filled to two digits)
* `[(,|.)s+]` is an optional string consisting of a comma or decimal point followed by numeric string of 1 or more digits, representing a fractional second
* `Z` is a literal meaning UTC (modern replacement for GMT), i.e. timezone `+0000`

valid_iso8601_date_time.name: valid_iso8601_date_time
valid_iso8601_date_time.description:
String is a valid ISO 8601 date-time, i.e. takes the form:

* `YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[(,|.)s+][Z|±hh[:mm]]` (extended)
* `YYYYMMDDThhmmss[(,|.)s+][Z|±hh[mm]]` (compact)
* or one of the partial forms:
** `YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm` or `YYYY-MM-DDThh` (extended)
** `YYYYMMDDThhmm` or `YYYYMMDDThh` (compact)

valid_iso8601_duration.name: valid_iso8601_duration
valid_iso8601_duration.description:
String is a valid ISO 8601 duration, i.e. takes the form:

* `P[nnY][nnM][nnW][nnD][T[nnH][nnM][nnS]]`

Where each nn represents a number of years, months, etc. nnW represents a number of 7-day weeks.

Note: allowing the `W` designator in the same expression as other designators is an exception to the published standard, but necessary in clinical information (typically for representing pregnancy duration).

Multiplicity_interval.name: Multiplicity_interval
Multiplicity_interval.description: An Interval of Integer, used to represent multiplicity, cardinality and optionality in models.

Multiplicity_range_marker.name: Multiplicity_range_marker
Multiplicity_range_marker.description: Marker to use in string form of interval between limits.

Multiplicity_unbounded_marker.name: Multiplicity_unbounded_marker
Multiplicity_unbounded_marker.description: Symbol to use to indicate upper limit unbounded.

is_open.name: is_open
is_open.description: True if this interval imposes no constraints, i.e. is set to `0..*`.

is_optional.name: is_optional
is_optional.description: True if this interval expresses optionality, i.e. `0..1`.

is_mandatory.name: is_mandatory
is_mandatory.description: True if this interval expresses mandation, i.e. `1..1`.

is_prohibited.name: is_prohibited
is_prohibited.description: True if this interval is set to `0..0`.

Proper_interval.name: Proper_interval
Proper_interval.description: Type representing a 'proper' Interval, i.e. any two-sided or one-sided interval.

Interval.name: Interval
Interval.description: Interval abstraction, featuring upper and lower limits that may be open or closed, included or not included.

lower_included.name: lower_included
lower_included.description: `lower` boundary value included in range if not `lower_unbounded`.

upper_included.name: upper_included
upper_included.description: `upper` boundary value included in range if not `upper_unbounded`.

has.name: has
has.description: True if `(lower_unbounded or lower_included and v >= lower) or v > lower and (upper_unbounded or upper_included and v <= upper or v < upper)`.

intersects.name: intersects
intersects.description: True if there is any overlap between intervals represented by Current and `other'. True if at least one limit of other is strictly inside the limits of this interval.

contains.name: contains
contains.description: True if current interval properly contains `other`? True if all points of `other` are inside the current interval.

is_equal.name: is_equal
is_equal.description: True if current object's interval is semantically same as `other`.

Limits_consistent.name: Limits_consistent
Limits_consistent.rule: (not upper_unbounded and not lower_unbounded) implies lower <= upper

Limits_comparable.name: Limits_comparable
Limits_comparable.rule: (not upper_unbounded and not lower_unbounded) implies lower.strictly_comparable_to (upper)

Point_interval.name: Point_interval
Point_interval.description: Type representing an Interval that happens to be a point value. Provides an efficient representation that is substitutable for `Interval<T>` where needed.

lower_included.name: lower_included
lower_included.description: lower boundary value included in range if not lower_unbounded.

upper_included.name: upper_included
upper_included.description: upper boundary value included in range if not upper_unbounded.

Cardinality.name: Cardinality
Cardinality.description: Express constraints on the cardinality of container objects which are the values of multiply-valued attributes, including uniqueness and ordering, providing the means to state that a container acts like a logical list, set or bag.

is_ordered.name: is_ordered
is_ordered.description: True if the members of the container attribute to which this cardinality refers are ordered.

is_unique.name: is_unique
is_unique.description: True if the members of the container attribute to which this cardinality refers are unique.

is_bag.name: is_bag
is_bag.description: True if the semantics of this cardinality represent a bag, i.e. unordered, non-unique membership.

is_list.name: is_list
is_list.description: True if the semantics of this cardinality represent a list, i.e. ordered, non-unique membership.

is_set.name: is_set
is_set.description: True if the semantics of this cardinality represent a set, i.e. unordered, unique membership.

Terminology_code.name: Terminology_code
Terminology_code.description: Logically primitive type representing a reference to a terminology concept, in the form of a terminology identifier, optional version, and a code or code string from the terminology.

terminology_id.name: terminology_id
terminology_id.description: The archetype environment namespace identifier used to identify a terminology. Typically a value like `"snomed_ct"` that is mapped elsewhere to the full URI identifying the terminology.

terminology_version.name: terminology_version
terminology_version.description: Optional string value representing terminology version, typically a date or dotted numeric.

code_string.name: code_string
code_string.description: A terminology code or post-coordinated code expression, if supported by the terminology. The code may refer to a single term, a value set consisting of multiple terms, or some other entity representable within the terminology.

uri.name: uri
uri.description: The URI reference that may be used as a concrete key into a notional terminology service for queries that can obtain the term text, definition, and other associated elements.

Terminology_term.name: Terminology_term
Terminology_term.description: Leaf type representing a term from a terminology, which consists of the term text and the code, i.e. a concept reference.

concept.name: concept
concept.description: Refrence to the terminology concept formally representing this term.

Any.name: Any
Any.description: Abstract supertype. Usually maps to a type like Any or Object in an object-oriented technology. Defined here to provide value and reference equality semantics.

instance_of.name: instance_of
instance_of.description: Create new instance of a type.

type_of.name: type_of
type_of.description: Type name of an object as a string. May include generic parameters, as in "Interval<Time>".

resource.name: resource
resource.description: The rm.common.resource package defines the structure and semantics of the general notion of an online resource which has been created by a human author, and consequently for which natural language is a factor.

AUTHORED_RESOURCE.name: AUTHORED_RESOURCE
AUTHORED_RESOURCE.description: Abstract idea of an online resource created by a human author.

uid.name: uid
uid.description: Unique identifier of the family of archetypes having the same interface identifier (same major version).

original_language.name: original_language
original_language.description: Language in which this resource was initially authored. Although there is no language primacy of resources overall, the language of original authoring is required to ensure natural language translations can preserve quality. Language is relevant in both the description and ontology sections.

description.name: description
description.description: Description and lifecycle information of the resource.

is_controlled.name: is_controlled
is_controlled.description: True if this resource is under any kind of change control (even file copying), in which case revision history is created.

annotations.name: annotations
annotations.description: Annotations on individual items within the resource, keyed by path. The inner table takes the form of a Hash table of String values keyed by String tags.

translations.name: translations
translations.description: List of details for each natural translation made of this resource, keyed by language code. For each translation listed here, there must be corresponding sections in all language-dependent parts of the resource. The `_original_language_` does not appear in this list.

current_revision.name: current_revision
current_revision.description: Most recent revision in revision_history if is_controlled else  (uncontrolled) .

languages_available.name: languages_available
languages_available.description: Total list of languages available in this resource, derived from original_language and translations.

Current_revision_valid.name: Current_revision_valid
Current_revision_valid.rule: (current_revision /= Void and not is_controlled) implies current_revision.is_equal ("(uncontrolled)")

Translations_valid.name: Translations_valid
Translations_valid.rule: translations /= Void implies (not translations.is_empty and not translations.has (orginal_language.code_string))

RESOURCE_DESCRIPTION.name: RESOURCE_DESCRIPTION
RESOURCE_DESCRIPTION.description: Defines the descriptive meta-data of a resource.

original_author.name: original_author
original_author.description: Original author of this resource, with all relevant details, including organisation.

original_namespace.name: original_namespace
original_namespace.description: Namespace of original author's organisation, in reverse internet form, if applicable.

original_publisher.name: original_publisher
original_publisher.description: Plain text name of organisation that originally published this artefact, if any.

other_contributors.name: other_contributors
other_contributors.description: Other contributors to the resource, each listed in "name <email>"  form.

lifecycle_state.name: lifecycle_state
lifecycle_state.description: Lifecycle state of the resource, typically including states such as: initial, in_development, in_review, published, superseded, obsolete.

custodian_namespace.name: custodian_namespace
custodian_namespace.description: Namespace in reverse internet id form, of current custodian organisation.

custodian_organisation.name: custodian_organisation
custodian_organisation.description: Plain text name of current custodian organisation.

copyright.name: copyright
copyright.description: Optional copyright statement for the resource as a knowledge resource.

licence.name: licence
licence.description: Licence of current artefact, in format "short licence name <URL of licence>", e.g. "Apache 2.0 License <http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0.html>"

ip_acknowledgements.name: ip_acknowledgements
ip_acknowledgements.description:
List of acknowledgements of other IP directly referenced in this archetype, typically terminology codes, ontology ids etc. Recommended keys are the widely known name or namespace for the IP source, as shown in the following example:

----
ip_acknowledgements = <
    ["loinc"] = <"This content from LOINC® is copyright © 1995 Regenstrief Institute, Inc. and the LOINC Committee, and available at no cost under the license at http://loinc.org/terms-of-use">
    ["snomedct"] = <"Content from SNOMED CT® is copyright © 2007 IHTSDO <ihtsdo.org>">
>
----

references.name: references
references.description: List of references of material on which this artefact is based, as a keyed list of strings. The keys should be in a standard citation format.

resource_package_uri.name: resource_package_uri
resource_package_uri.description: URI of package to which this resource belongs.

conversion_details.name: conversion_details
conversion_details.description:
Details related to conversion process that generated this model from an original, if relevant, as a list of name/value pairs. Typical example with recommended tags:

----
conversion_details = <
    ["source_model"] = <"CEM model xyz <http://location.in.clinicalelementmodels.com>">
    ["tool"] = <"cem2adl v6.3.0">
    ["time"] = <"2014-11-03T09:05:00">
>
----

other_details.name: other_details
other_details.description: Additional non-language-sensitive resource meta-data, as a list of name/value pairs.

details.name: details
details.description: Details of all parts of resource description that are natural language-dependent, keyed by language code.

TRANSLATION_DETAILS.name: TRANSLATION_DETAILS
TRANSLATION_DETAILS.description: Class providing details of a natural language translation.

language.name: language
language.description: Language of the translation, coded using ISO 639-1 (2 character) language codes.

author.name: author
author.description: Translator name and other demographic details.

accreditaton.name: accreditaton
accreditaton.description: Accreditation of translator, usually a national translator's registration or association membership id.

version_last_translated.name: version_last_translated
version_last_translated.description: Version of this resource last time it was translated into the language represented by this `TRANSLATION_DETAILS` object.

RESOURCE_DESCRIPTION_ITEM.name: RESOURCE_DESCRIPTION_ITEM
RESOURCE_DESCRIPTION_ITEM.description: Language-specific detail of resource description. When a resource is translated for use in another language environment, each `RESOURCE_DESCRIPTION_ITEM` needs to be copied and translated into the new language.

language.name: language
language.description: The localised language in which the items in this description item are written. Coded using ISO 639-1 (2 character) language codes.

keywords.name: keywords
keywords.description: Keywords which characterise this resource, used e.g. for indexing and searching.

use.name: use
use.description: Description of the uses of the resource, i.e. contexts in which it could be used.

misuse.name: misuse
misuse.description: Description of any misuses of the resource, i.e. contexts in which it should not be used.

original_resource_uri.name: original_resource_uri
original_resource_uri.description: URIs of original clinical document(s) or description of which resource is a formalisation, in the language of this description item; keyed by meaning.

other_details.name: other_details
other_details.description: Additional language-senstive resource metadata, as a list of name/value pairs.

RESOURCE_ANNOTATIONS.name: RESOURCE_ANNOTATIONS
RESOURCE_ANNOTATIONS.description:
Object representing annotations on an archetype. These can be of various forms, with a documentation form defined so far, which has a multi-level tabular structure [ [ [String value, String key], path key], language key]. Example instance, showing the documentation structure.

--------
    documentation = <
        ["en"] = <
           ["/data[id2]"] = <
               ["ui"] = <"passthrough">
           >
           ["/data[id2]/items[id3]"] = <
               ["design note"] = <"this is a design note on Statement">
               ["requirements note"] = <"this is a requirements note on Statement">
               ["medline ref"] = <"this is a medline ref on Statement">
           >
        >
    >
--------

Other sub-structures might have different keys, e.g.  based on programming languages, UI toolkits etc.

documentation.name: documentation
documentation.description: Documentary annotations in a multi-level keyed structure.
